In Kenya for instance, youth in the 18-35 age bracket constitute about 40 per cent of the population with the number projected to increase.Kenya should realise the goals articulated in the strategy by creating infrastructure and networks to educate and involve youth in activities related to global trade, diplomacy, sustainability and peace-building. There has been heightened activities by the global players to create common grounds to promote prosperity as well as address a myriad of problems facing humanity in the wake of growing technology that has increasingly made the world a global village in recent years.
Unfortunately for young people, who hold key to the success of the ongoing initiatives, due to their sheer numbers, technological advancement and their roles in today’s social economic order have largely been ignored at the diplomatic level.



