The strategy incorporates the role of youth in development initiatives and significant contribution to the overall economic development and diplomacy. At its core, the strategy aims to provide a blueprint for joint initiatives and implementation of effective practices before it is too late.
It also outlines of ensuring protection and support for young people, and provides a platform through which their “needs can be addressed, their voice can be amplified, and their engagement can be advanced.
Kenya should realise the goals articulated in the strategy by creating infrastructure and networks to educate and involve youth in activities related to global trade, diplomacy, sustainability and peace-building.
The more challenging goal will be enacting long-term policy reforms that empower youth and provide them with skills sets to confidently navigate the world of international politics, before negative consequences of lack of youth engagement in diplomacy manifests.
